<PLACE><ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">New York</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX></PLACE>
<SBODY>1 2
Liber 184.
WARRANTY <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">DEED</ENAMEX>. -- Chap. 478, <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1890</TIMEX>.
This <ENAMEX TYPE="EVENT.xlife">Indenture</ENAMEX>, Made the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">twenty-fifth day of ⌨⌨⌨ in the year
eighteen hundred and ninety four</TIMEX> Between <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Lottie E. Yaw</ENAMEX> of <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">East Otto</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Cattaraugus
County</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>.
of the first part, and mansion <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Potter</ENAMEX> of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of Ashford</ENAMEX>, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF.loc">State and County aforesaid</ENAMEX>
of the second
ond part, Witnesseth,
That the said party of the first part, for and in consideration of the sum of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">Three hundred and seventy five $ 3750/100 ) Dollars</NUMEX>,
lawful money of the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">United States</ENAMEX>, paid by the said party of the second part, does hereby grant and release unto the said party of the second
part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">her</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever,
ALL THAT TRACT OR PARCEL OF LAND, situate in the <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">Town of Ashford</ENAMEX> of
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">County of Cattaraugus</ENAMEX>,
and <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">State of New York</ENAMEX>, distinguished as being part of lot number sixty two in township
number five in the sixth range of townships of the <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION">Holland Land Company</ENAMEX>'s survey
and bounded as follows: Commencincing at the north east comer of lands deeded by
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Calvin Woodruff</ENAMEX> to the <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">trustees</ENAMEX> of the first fire will Buttist Society of the <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Ashford</ENAMEX>, thence northerly along the highway <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty</NUMEX> links, thence south
<NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">sixty two & three fourths</NUMEX> arances west <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">two</NUMEX> chains and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">thirty seven and one half</NUMEX> links,
thence northerly parallel to the first mentioned boundary <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one</NUMEX> chain and <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">fifty</NUMEX> links,
thence Easterly on lands of the said free will <ENAMEX TYPE="ORGANIZATION.rel">Baptist Society</ENAMEX> <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">two</NUMEX> chains <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">thirty seven
and one half</NUMEX> links, to the place of beginning, containing <NUMEX TYPE="QUANTITY">one third</NUMEX> of an acre
more or less.
the party of the filing that and Ente this conveyance will sell to a mortgage
of <NUMEX TYPE="MONEY">seventy five dollars</NUMEX> which remains in said given to buquata <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">su</ENAMEX> ackenbush
assigned to Shebect matter <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> is now the owner. and the said party of the
second part agrees to pay the said mortgage within the next <ENAMEX TYPE="DURATANNIV">two years</ENAMEX> with
and interest,
Together, with the appurtenances; and all the estate and rights of the said part of the first part, in and to said premises. To have and to hold.
the above granted premises unto the said part of the second part, <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">heirs</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">assigns</ENAMEX> forever.
And the said <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">R.B. You</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Dollie</ENAMEX> & do covenant with the said party of the second part as follows:
That the party of the second part shall quitly enjoy the said premises.
That the said Parties of the lout part
will forever warrant the Title to said premises.
In <ENAMEX TYPE="NONFAMILY">Witness</ENAMEX> Wilbereof, the said parties of the first part have hereunto set the hand - and seal the <TIMEX TYPE="COREF.dat">day and year first above written</TIMEX>.
In the presence of
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">R.B. Wall</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">[ L. S.]
Dotter</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">E. Yaw</ENAMEX> ( S.)
<ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">STATE OF NEW YORK</ENAMEX>. <ENAMEX TYPE="LOCALE">COUNTY OF Town of East Otho</ENAMEX>
On the <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">24 - day of January
in the year eighteen
hundred and ninety</TIMEX> before <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX>, personally came <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">R.B. Yaw</ENAMEX> and <ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Dollie E.</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">his</ENAMEX> <ENAMEX TYPE="FAMILYMEMBER">wife</ENAMEX>
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> known and known to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> to be the individual described in, and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">who</ENAMEX> executed the foregoing instrument and <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> thereupon Each duely acknowledged
to <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">me</ENAMEX> that <ENAMEX TYPE="COREF">they</ENAMEX> executed the same.
℗
<ENAMEX TYPE="PERSON">Edwin F. Beebe</ENAMEX>
<ENAMEX TYPE="OCCUPATION">Notary Public</ENAMEX>
Sadies, day of ember <TIMEX TYPE="DATE">1800</TIMEX> ▓ ▓ ---\+
</SBODY>
</NBX>
